HEADWORD: Tautomerism
<hw>Tau*tom"er*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/; <?/,
for <?/ <?/ the same + <?/ part.]</ety> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>The
condition, quality, or relation of metameric substances, or their
respective derivatives, which are more or less interchangeable,
according as one form or the other is the more stable. It is a special
case of metamerism; thus, the lactam and the lactim compounds exhibit
<xex>tautomerism</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

